# API Endpoint Update Rules

## Adding a New API Endpoint

1. Add handler function in `main.go`
2. Add route in `main.go`
3. Update `docs/API.md`:
   - Add endpoint section with full description
   - Include request/response examples
   - Document error responses
4. Update `docs/openapi.yaml`:
   - Add path definition
   - Add request/response schemas
   - Add examples
   - Add error responses

## Modifying an Existing Endpoint

1. Update handler in `main.go`
2. Update `docs/API.md`:
   - Update endpoint description
   - Update request/response examples
   - Update error responses if changed
3. Update `docs/openapi.yaml`:
   - Update path definition
   - Update schemas if response format changed
   - Update examples
